# ü§ñ AI Browser Automation Suite
### Proof of Concept (POC)

[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.10%2B-blue?logo=python&logoColor=white)](https://www.python.org/)
[![Playwright](https://img.shields.io/badge/Playwright-Latest-green?logo=playwright&logoColor=white)](https://playwright.dev/)
[![Gemini](https://img.shields.io/badge/AI-Gemini%202.0%20Flash-8E75B2?logo=google&logoColor=white)](https://deepmind.google/technologies/gemini/)
[![MCP](https://img.shields.io/badge/Protocol-MCP-orange)](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/)

**A dual-mode AI testing framework combining Interactive Chat with Autonomous Workflows.**

Powered by Google Gemini 2.0 Flash, Playwright, and the Model Context Protocol.
---

## üåü Key Features

| Feature | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| **üó£Ô∏è Interactive Chat** | Control the browser manually using natural language commands (e.g., *"Go to Google and search for Playwright"*). |
| **üî¥ Auto-Recording** | Automatically converts your chat actions into ready-to-run **Playwright TypeScript** test code (`.spec.ts`). |
| **‚ö° Autonomous Architect** | Loads test scenarios from Markdown files (`fixture/tests/`) and executes steps automatically without human intervention. |
| **üõ†Ô∏è Self-Healing** | The AI agent detects errors, analyzes the DOM, and automatically retries failed steps with corrected selectors. |

---

## üöÄ Getting Started

Follow these steps to set up the architecture locally.

### üìã Prerequisites
*   **Python 3.10+**
*   **Node.js 18+** & **npm**
*   **Google API Key** (Required for Gemini Model)

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Setup Playwright Server (MCP)
This server acts as the bridge between the AI and the browser.

```bash
cd playwright-server

# Install Node dependencies
npm install

# Install Browser Binaries (Critical Step)
npx playwright install

cd ../python-client

# Create Virtual Environment
python3 -m venv venv

# Activate Virtual Environment
# Mac/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate
# Windows:
# venv\Scripts\activate

# Install Python Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
